 <title ixia_locid="1">Introduction to System Administration</title>
 <shortdesc ixia_locid="2">System administration for the Titanium Server involves system-level configuration and
  management of the physical nodes within the cloud.</shortdesc>
 <prolog>
  <author ixia_locid="3">Randall Budd</author>
 </prolog>
 <conbody>
  <p ixia_locid="4">System administration includes the following functions:</p>
  <ul id="ul_mnw_g3h_tw">
   <li ixia_locid="5">
    <p ixia_locid="6">configuration of the physical nodes</p>
   </li>
   <li ixia_locid="7">
    <p ixia_locid="8">node connection management</p>
   </li>
   <li ixia_locid="9">
    <p ixia_locid="10">network configuration</p>
   </li>
   <li ixia_locid="11">
    <p ixia_locid="12">fault and resource usage monitoring of the physical nodes</p>
   </li>
   <li ixia_locid="13">
    <p ixia_locid="14">backup and restore of the physical nodes</p>
   </li>
  </ul>
  <note conref="jcj1480616461300.xml#jcj1480616461300/note_N10012_N1000F_N10001" id="note_N1005E_N1001F_N10001" ixia_locid="15"/>
